# Documentation Standards - SD-DarkMaster-Unified

## 📚 Documentation Structure (MANDATORY)

All documentation MUST follow the numbered importance system in `SD-DarkMaster-Unified/Docs/`:

### Numbered Documentation System
- **01-06 Essential:** Core project documents (README, Architecture, Technical, etc.)
- **07-09 UI Focused:** Interface and user experience documents
- **10 Support:** Troubleshooting and maintenance
- **11-12 AI-Maintained:** Dynamic status tracking (AUTO-UPDATED)
- **13 Meta:** Documentation navigation

### Reference Format
- ALWAYS reference documents by number: `01_README.md`, NOT `README.md`
- ALWAYS use full numbered filenames in links and references
- NEVER reference outdated 5-cell architecture documents

## 🤖 AI-Maintained Documents

### Auto-Update Requirements
These documents MUST be updated automatically by AI agents:

#### [11_DYNAMIC_STATE_PROMPT.md](mdc:SD-DarkMaster-Unified/Docs/11_DYNAMIC_STATE_PROMPT.md)
- **Update Triggers:** Major changes, status updates, feature completion
- **Format:** UTC timestamps, semantic versioning, changelog entries
- **Content:** Real-time project status, metrics, current development

#### [12_AI_HANDOVER_DOCUMENT.md](mdc:SD-DarkMaster-Unified/Docs/12_AI_HANDOVER_DOCUMENT.md)
- **Update Triggers:** Architecture changes, major context shifts
- **Format:** Version tracking, context preservation
- **Content:** Session context, recent changes, technical state

### AI Agent Responsibilities
- Update AI-maintained documents after significant changes
- Increment version numbers using semantic versioning
- Add changelog entries with clear descriptions
- Cross-reference with related documents
- Maintain UTC timestamps for all entries

## 📝 Documentation Quality Standards

### Required Elements
- **Numbered Filename:** All docs must be numbered 01-13
- **Clear Purpose:** Explicit purpose statement in each document
- **Target Audience:** Clearly defined audience and prerequisites
- **Cross-References:** Links use numbered format (e.g., `[01_README.md](01_README.md)`)
- **Update Tracking:** Last updated timestamps in UTC

### Maintenance Rules
- Keep all documentation current with unified single-cell architecture
- Remove any references to obsolete 5-cell architecture
- Update cross-references when documents are modified
- Maintain consistency with [13_DOCUMENTATION_INDEX.md](mdc:SD-DarkMaster-Unified/Docs/13_DOCUMENTATION_INDEX.md)

## 🚫 Prohibited Actions

### NEVER Do These
- Create documentation outside `SD-DarkMaster-Unified/Docs/` folder
- Reference documents without numbers (use `01_README.md`, not `README.md`)
- Skip updating AI-maintained documents after major changes
- Create duplicate documentation files
- Reference obsolete 5-cell architecture

### Documentation Anti-Patterns
- Unnumbered documents
- Scattered documentation across multiple folders
- Outdated cross-references
- Missing AI-maintained status updates
- Inconsistent formatting between documents

## ✅ Validation Checklist

Before committing documentation changes:
- [ ] All documents numbered correctly (01-13)
- [ ] AI-maintained documents updated if needed
- [ ] Cross-references use numbered format
- [ ] Documentation index reflects changes
- [ ] No references to obsolete 5-cell architecture
- [ ] UTC timestamps updated
- [ ] Quality standards met (purpose, audience, prerequisites)

---

**This rule ensures all documentation follows the established numbered system and maintains the unified single-cell architecture standards.**